        "question": "<p>If \\(\\frac{3x^2 + 3x - 2}{(x - 1)(x + 1)}\\) = P + \\(\\frac{Q}{x - 1} + \\frac{R}{x - 1}\\) </p><p>Find the value of Q and R </p>",
        "answer": "<p>\\(\\frac{3x^2 + 3x - 2}{(x - 1)(x + 1)}\\) = P + \\(\\frac{Q}{x - 1} + \\frac{R}{x - 1}\\) </p><p>Long division</p><table border=\"1\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" style=\"width:500px\">\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td>\n<p>\\(x^2 - 1\\)</p>\n</td>\n<td> 3</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td> </td>\n<td>\n<p> 3x\\(^2\\) + 3x - 2</p>\n<p> -(3x\\(^2\\) - 3x)</p>\n<p>\\(\\overline{6x - 2}\\)</p>\n<p> </p>\n<p> </p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table><p> </p><p>\\(\\frac{6x^{-2}}{(x - 1)(x + 1)}\\)</p><p>= \\(\\frac{Q}{x - 1} + \\frac{R}{x + 1}\\)</p><p>6x - 2 = Q (x + 1) + R(x - 1)</p><p>Let x = -1 </p><p>6(-1) - 2 = Q(-1 + 1) + R (-1 - 1)</p><p>-6 - 2 = -2R</p><p>\\(\\frac{-8}{-2} = \\frac{-2R}{-2}\\) </p><p>R = 4</p><p>From 6x - 2 = Q(x - 1) + R(x - 1)</p><p>Let x = 1</p><p>6(1) - 2 = Q(1 + 1) + R(1 - 1) </p><p>6 - 2 = 2Q </p><p>\\(\\frac{4}{2} = \\frac{2Q}{2}\\)</p><p>= Q = 2</p>",
        "type": "theory"
    },
