        "question": "<p>Given that w = 8i + 3j, x = 6i - 5j, y = 2i + 3j and |z| = 41. find z in the direction of w + x - 2y.</p>",
        "answer": "<p>W = 8i + 3J</p><p>X = 6i - 5J </p><p>Y = 2i + 3J</p><p>w + x - 2y = 8i + 3j + 6i - 5j - 2(2i + 3j)</p><p>= 10i - 8j</p><p>Z = \\(\\frac{10i - 8j}{|Z|}\\)</p><p>= \\(\\frac{10i - 8j}{4}\\)</p><p>= \\(\\frac{10i}{4}\\)</p><p>\\(\\frac{8j}{4}\\)</p><p>= \\(\\frac{5}{2}\\)i - 2j</p>",
