        "question": "<p>(a) Find the derivative of y = x\\(^2\\) (1 + x)\\(^{\\frac{3}{2}}\\) with respect to x.</p><p>(b) The centre of a circle lies on the line 2y - x = 3. If the circle passes through P(2,3) and Q(6,7), find its equation.</p>",
        "answer": "<p>y = x\\(^2\\)(1 + x)\\(^{\\frac{3}{2}}\\)</p><p>Let u = x\\(^2\\) </p><p>v = (1 + x)\\(^{\\frac{3}{2}}\\)</p><p>\\(\\frac{du}{dx} 2x\\)</p><p>\\(\\frac{dv}{dx} = \\frac{3}{2}\\)(1 + x)\\(^\\frac{1}{2}\\)</p><p>\\(\\frac{dy}{dx} = v\\frac{du}{dx} + u\\frac{dv}{dx}\\) </p><p>= (1 + x)\\(^{\\frac{3}{2}}\\)(2x) + x\\(^2\\)\\(\\frac{3}{2}(1 + x)^{\\frac{1}{2}}\\)</p><p>= 2x(1 + x)\\(^{\\frac{3}{2}}\\) + \\(\\frac{3x^2(1 + x)^{\\frac{1}{2}}}{2}\\)</p><p> </p><p> </p><p>(b) </p><p>2y - x = 3</p><p>when x = 0, y  = \\(\\frac{3}{2}\\)</p><p>when y = 0, x = -3</p><p>h = -3, k = \\(\\frac{3}{2}\\)</p><p>Using </p><p>(x - h)\\(^2\\) + (y - k)\\(^2\\)  = r\\(^2\\) </p><p>(x + 3)\\(^2\\)  + (y - \\(\\frac{3}{2}\\))\\(^2\\)  = r\\(^2\\) </p><p>r(2, 3), x = 2, y = 3</p><p>(2 + 3)\\(^2\\)  + (3 + \\(\\frac{3}{2}\\))\\(^2\\)  = r\\(^2\\) </p><p>\\(\\frac{109}{4}\\) = r\\(^2\\)  </p><p>The equation will give </p><p>(x + 3)\\(^2\\)  + (y - \\(\\frac{3}{2}\\))\\(^2\\)  </p><p>= \\(\\frac{109}{4}\\)</p>",
        "type": "theory"
    },
    {
