        "year": 2020,
        "question": "<p>(a) Simplify; \\(\\frac{log_2 ^8 + log_2 ^{16} - 4 log_2 ^2}{log_4^{16}}\\)</p><p>(b) The first, third, and seventh terms of an Arithmetic Progression (A.P) from three consecutive terms of a Geometric Progression (G.P). If the sum of the first two terms of the A.P is 6, find its:</p><p>(I) first term; (ii) common difference.</p>",
        "answer": "<p>\\(\\frac{log_2 ^8 + log_2 ^ {16} - 4 log_2^ 2}{log_4^{16}}\\)</p><p>= \\(\\frac{3log_2 ^2 + 4 log_2^ 2 - 4 log_2 2}{2 log_4^4}\\)</p><p>= \\(\\frac{3 + 4 - 4}{2}\\) </p><p>= \\(\\frac{3}{2}\\) </p><p> </p><p>(b) </p><table border=\"1\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" style=\"width:500px\">\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td>AP</td>\n<td>GP</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>\n<p>T\\(_1\\)</p>\n<p>T\\(_3\\)</p>\n<p>T\\(_7\\)</p>\n</td>\n<td>\n<p>T\\(_1\\)</p>\n<p>T\\(_2\\)</p>\n<p>T\\(_3\\)</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table><p> </p><p>T\\(_1\\) + T\\(_2\\) = 6</p><p>a + a + d = 6</p><p>2a + d = 6.....(i)</p><p>a = a</p><p>a + 2d = ar, a + 6d = ar\\(^2\\)</p><p>\\(\\frac{a + 2d}{a} = \\frac{a + 6d}{a + 2d}\\)</p><p>(a + 2d)\\(^2\\)  = \\(\\frac{a + 6d}{a + 2d}\\)</p><p>(a + 2d)\\(^2\\) = a(a + 6d)</p><p>a\\(^2\\) + 4d\\(^2\\) + 4ad = a\\(^2\\) + 6ad</p><p>4d\\(^2\\) = 6ad - 4ad</p><p>4d\\(^2\\) = 2ad</p><p>\\(\\frac{4d}{2} = \\frac{2a}{2}\\)</p><p>a = 2d ......(ii)</p><p>from;</p><p>2a + d = 6</p><p>2(2d) + d = 6</p><p>4d + d = 6</p><p>5d = 6</p><p>d = \\(\\frac{6}{5}\\) </p><p>= 1\\(\\frac{1}{5}\\) </p><p>from; a = 2d</p><p>a = \\(\\frac{2 \\times 6}{5}\\) </p><p>= \\(\\frac{12}{5}\\)</p><p>= 2\\(\\frac{2}{5}\\) </p><p>First term = 2\\(\\frac{2}{5}\\) </p><p>Common difference = 1\\(\\frac{4}{5}\\) </p><p> </p>",
        "type": "theory"
    },
