        "question": "<p>(a) An association is made up of 6 farmers and 8 traders. If an executive body of 4 members is to be formed, find the probability that it will consist of at least two farmers. (b) The probability of an accident occurring in a given month in factories X, Y, and Z are \\(\\frac{1}{5}, \\frac{1}{12} \\) and \\(\\frac{1}{6}\\) respectively.</p><p>Find the probability that the accident will occur in:</p><p>i) none of the factories;</p><p>(ii) all the factories;</p><p>(iii) at least one factory.</p><p> </p>",
        "answer": "<p>No. of farmers = 6</p><p>No. of traders = 8</p><p>Total = 14 </p><p>Pr(at least two farmers)</p><p>= \\(\\frac{^6C_2 \\times ^8C_2}{^{14}C_4} + \\frac{^6C_3 \\times ^8C_1}{^{14}}+ \\frac{^6C_4 \\times ^8C_0}{^{14}C_4}\\)</p><p>= \\(\\frac{15 \\times 28}{1001} + \\frac{20 \\times 8}{1001} + \\frac{15 \\times 1}{1001}\\)</p><p>= \\(\\frac{420}{1001} + \\frac{160}{1001} + \\frac{15}{1001}\\) </p><p>= \\(\\frac{420 + 160 + 15}{1001}\\)</p><p>= \\(\\frac{595}{1001}\\) </p><p> </p><p>(b) P(x) = \\(\\frac{1}{5}\\) </p><p>p(x\\(^1\\)) = 1 - \\(\\frac{1}{5}\\) = \\(\\frac{4}{5}\\)</p><p>p(y) = \\(\\frac{1}{2}\\), p(y\\(^1\\))</p><p>= 1 - \\(\\frac{1}{12}\\)</p><p>= \\(\\frac{11}{12}\\)</p><p>p(2) = \\(\\frac{1}{6}\\)</p><p>p(z\\(^1\\)) = 1 - \\(\\frac{1}{6}\\)</p><p>= \\(\\frac{5}{6}\\) </p><p> </p><p>(i) Pr() </p><p>= \\(\\frac{4}{5} \\times \\frac{11}{12} \\times \\frac{5}{6} = \\frac{11}{18}\\)</p><p> </p><p>(ii) Pr(all the factories)</p><p>= \\(\\frac{1}{5} \\times \\frac{1}{12} \\times \\frac{1}{6} = \\frac{1}{360^o}\\) </p><p> </p><p>(iii) Pr (at least one factory)</p><p>= 1 - Pr (none) = \\(\\frac{1}{1} - \\frac{11}{18}\\)</p><p>= \\(\\frac{18 - 11}{18}\\)</p><p>= \\(\\frac{7}{18}\\)</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>",
        "type": "theory"
    },
