        "answer": "<p>(a) u = 10ms\\(^{-1}\\), a = 0.2m\\(^{-2}\\), s = 100m, t = ? </p><p>using S = ut + \\(\\frac{1}{2} at^2\\)</p><p>100 = 10t + \\(\\frac{1}{2}(0.2)t^2\\)</p><p>100 = 10t + 0.1t\\(^2\\)</p><p>0.1t\\(^2\\) + 10t - 100 = 0</p><p>t = \\(\\frac{-10 \\pm \\sqrt{10^2 - 4(0.1)(-100)}}{2(0.1)}\\)</p><p>t = \\(\\frac{-10\\pm \\sqrt{100 + 40}}{0.2}\\)</p><p>t = \\(\\frac{-10 \\pm \\sqrt{140}}{0.2}\\)</p><p>t = \\(\\frac{-10 \\pm 11.83}{0.2}\\)</p><p>t = \\(\\frac{-10 - 11.82}{2}\\)</p><p>t = \\(\\frac{1.83}{0.2}\\) </p><p>t = \\(\\frac{21.83}{2}\\) </p><p>t = 9.15 seconds</p><p> </p><p>(b)(i) S = t\\(^2\\) - 5 + 6</p><p>v =  \\(\\frac{ds}{dt}\\)</p><p>= 2t - 5</p><p>at t = 0, y = 2(0) - 5</p><p>= - 5ms\\(^{-1}\\)</p><p>The initial velocity is 5 in the negative direction </p><p> </p><p>(ii) When t = 0, S = t\\(^2\\) - 5t + 6</p><p>S = 0\\(^2\\) - 5(0) + 6 </p><p>S = 6</p><p>The distance is 6m</p>",
